@adriancole When using "java -jar zipkin-server-2.16.2-exec.jar --logging.level.zipkin2=TRACE", I get no log at all when the server receives traces or displays them in Lens.
Is this the expected behavior ?
Is there a way to get debugs and traces showing what Zipkin server is doing (to learn about Zipkin internals)?

you'll need to get this into your classpath and set a property to use it via the docs in zipkin-server README. I'm closing this issue as I don't expect us to generalize this at this point.

```java
import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.TreeNode;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.UncheckedIOException;
import org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.Deserializer;
import org.apache.kafka.common.utils.Bytes;

public final class UnwrappingJsonDeserializer implements Deserializer<Bytes> {
  static final ObjectMapper OBJECT_MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    String span = "{\n"
      + "  \"traceId\": \"6b221d5bc9e6496c\",\n"
      + "  \"id\": \"6b221d5bc9e6496c\"\n"
      + "}";
    String json = "{\"message\": " + span + "}";

    Bytes decoded = new UnwrappingJsonDeserializer().deserialize(null, json.getBytes());
    System.err.println(new String(decoded.get()));
  }

  @Override public Bytes deserialize(String topic, byte[] data) {
    if (data == null || data.length == 0) return null;
    try {
      TreeNode tree = OBJECT_MAPPER.readTree(data).at("/message");
      return Bytes.wrap(tree.toString().getBytes());
    } catch (IOException e) {
      throw new UncheckedIOException(e); // unexpected with a byte array
    }
  }
}
```

