> This looks very good. I'd assume at some point we will have Dependencies also as an independent module, and we would need a way to have different back-end supporting different parts of the storage; am I following correctly?

We can pull out Dependencies as another module, in fact we started towards that with links query. However, we don't have a complete use case likely to be merged about that. Anyway, I think it will eventually happen and can follow similarly to this.

`ZipkinServerConfiguration` has a magic number:

```
      // It's common for backend requests to have timeouts of the magic number 10s, so we go ahead
      // and default to a slightly longer timeout on the server to be able to handle these with
      // better error messages where possible.
      sb.requestTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(11));
```

